Grede Holdings Seeks $175 Million Loan to Pay Dividend to Owner

-- B y   R i c h a r d   B r a v o
-- 
2011-03-16T15:21:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/grede-holdings-seeks-175-million-loan-to-pay-dividend-to-owner.html
Grede Holdings LLC, a supplier of
metal components to transportation and industrial markets, is
seeking a $175 million term loan B to pay a dividend to its
financial sponsor, according to  Standard & Poor’s .  S&P assigned the six-year loan a preliminary grade of B+,
according to a report by the rating company. Grede, based in
Southfield, Michigan is controlled by the private-equity firm
Wayzata Investment Partners LLC, according to the company’s
 website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Bravo in  New York  at 
 rbravo5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 